Sports Illustrated offers insight from around the league, including potential trades involving Bryce Young and Cooper Kupp. NBC Sports outlines the schedule and rules for the deadline, and several news outlets, including USA TODAY and the Detroit Free Press, provide up-to-date rumors and analysis on the latest developments. The Dallas Cowboys and New York Jets are among the teams with the most recent news and rumors leading up to the deadline.

Irvine, California, will have a Veterans Day Ceremony, and the Arkansas House of Representatives will hold its own celebration. Wellesley, Massachusetts, and Redmond, Washington, will both observe Veterans Day with special events.

summary: Multiple significant legal and policy developments have emerged. The House is poised to vote on a bill abolishing the Windfall Elimination Provision and other Social Security clauses. New York's highest court has upheld an absentee ballot law aimed at increasing voter turnout. A provision in the estate tax law is unlikely to benefit the majority of people due to income limitations. The 2024 Most Influential Woman in Volusia-Flagler was recognized for her organization, Provision Packs. A "poison pill" provision in the NBA will impact 11 players in 2024-25. The New York Times' "Connections" puzzle has clues and answers for November 4th. The United Methodist Church has rejected a provision allowing churches to leave the denomination easily. Sberbank's quarterly profit has declined due to tax adjustments and increased provisions. Delaware's Court of Chancery has provided guidance on earnout provisions in recent cases. Lastly, the Supreme Court has authorized Virginia to remove suspected non-citizens from voter rolls.

name: Voter registration
summary: Various news articles highlight issues related to voter registration in the United States. In Pennsylvania, suspicious voter registration forms have been linked to an Arizona activist's company, while a Virginia purge has removed U.S. citizens from voter rolls. In Pennsylvania's Lancaster County, fraudulent voter registrations have sparked a blame game between Left and Right. These issues have been accompanied by a wave of misinformation, further complicating the situation. Additionally, concerns have been raised about the new voter system in Nevada, while Oklahoma has seen record-breaking early voting and voter registration. Despite these challenges, most states trail behind 2020 levels in youth voter registration, just a week away from the election.
